Joel Wilkinson, from Hull, was diagnosed with Duchenne Muscular Dystrophy six months ago .
His parents, Emma, 33, and Chris, 36, noticed he was struggling to develop and learn to walk .
They were devastated when tests confirmed he had the incurable disease .
He will eventually need a wheelchair and has a life expectancy of just 20 years .
But his sister, Phoebe, five, plays only 'muscle friendly' games that won't tire her brother .
She helps him put on his shoes, fasten up his coat and fetch him cereal .